  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Communication for Regional Livelihood Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at strengthening Regional capacities to deliver communication products and processes around the LH work. The project emerges from the recognition of LAC global leadership around three main areas: new business models to engage the private sector; analytical tools to incorporate CCA in LH and WEL. The project will finance the development of content, channels, messaging, and the production in four priority areas: (i) more trasparent, fair and equitable markets, (ii) raising awareness and creating solutions for CCA; (iii) supporting the new EJ campaign, and (iv) supporting the livelihood work on Gender Justice</narrative>
  </description>
